channel.title: Help with teleports please!
channel.description:
Hi, I need help with teleports! Nobody has tried to help me so far except for Project Evolution, but I still cannot find out how to do this.
I know how to change teleports from the emote tab, but I am unsure of how to change teleports on the mage tab. For example, I want Varrock to teleport to a training area instead of Varrock. I have right-clicked it and tried to find the number that showed up in my Client.Java, but I could not find it. I also tried looking at the command prompt after I teleported. I tried to find that number in my Client.Java, but I was out of luck also. I AM USING DELTASCAPE!
Can someone please help me, and tell me what to do? Thanks!
~Jc22493
P.S. - I'm not going to be a noob and say, "If you give me a good answer, I will rep you!", because I can't rep yet, and I won't lie about it.
Thanks again!

item.title: Help with teleports please!
item.dc:creator: @Project_Evolution Project Evolution
item.description:
@Project_Evolution wrote:

I just figured it out for the Varrock teleport to Home. It was really easy, but tricky to find.

In your clickingMost.java search for,

case 4140

You should see,

case 73100: case 4140: case 50235: c.triggerTele(2999+misc.random(3), 3377+misc.random(3), 0); break;

Packet 50235 is the dialogue for the home teleport. Now see the 2999 and the 3377? Those are the coordinate’s. The misc.randoms are just extra coordinate’s. Leave those.

So again, just change the 2999 and 3377 coordinate’s.
